#######################################################################
#
# Commit message recommendation
# -----------------------------
#
# [MODULE] A short but descriptive summary
#
# A comprehensible description of why you did this work. Do not limit
# yourself here.
#
# The width of the description is arbitrary, but it's a good idea to 
# wrap the text by 72 chars.
#
# Examples:
# ---------
#
# - [MODULE] tag should be the name of a CMake module in the engine
#   source code in all caps, e.g. [FOUNDATION]
# - The summary should be imperative (not past tense) and not end with
#   period, e.g. Add timer class
# - Description of a commit should explain why a change was made.
#   e.g. The engine requires timing to function properly.
#
#######################################################################
